<br>
Food for thought:<br>
<br>
SoT has 74 active Planar Level members. Yes, we keep close watch on this, in case you want to know.<br>
<br>
We usually have 30 at a Fear Raid, cause that's all that are on-line at the time.<br>
<br>
That's about half, and most are level 60.<br>
<br>
If a guild, who is JUST reaching Planar Levels, and has only 30, let's say they can field 15. How do they expect to do it?<br>
<br>
Don't say &quot;ask another guild&quot;, cause you can only have 6 from any other entity, else they'll be breaking that 'rule'.<br>
<br>
IF they have their 15, and 30 from various other guilds, then how it is *their* Raid?  (And this would prompt putting the 2/3 rule back into place).<br>
<br>
If they go in with their 15, and get wiped out, and ask another guild to CR them, and then &quot;help&quot; them do Fear, this would also not be *their* Raid.<br>
<br>
This type of abuse is why the 40 to post was put into place, and has been working fine.<br>
<br>
