<br>
1 Guild amasses at portal<br>
2 Guild sets up groups, the first two (or so) being those that can kill mobs very fast, second wave, those who can assist the first grp, feed mana, heal etc. Third wave, simmilar to second, and so on.<br>
3 Guild zones in, turns left (in some cases Kayans go right and train unhappies)<br>
4 Guild gets to WW after losing half their grp.<br>
5 Guild fights mobs, takes 3 or 4 down then dies.<br>
6 Guild amasses at portal<br>
repeat steps 2-5<br>
7 guild calls in another guild to assist<br>
<br>
This is not a way to start off a fear raid. It is my opinion that if you dont have 4 or 5 warriors, 4 or 5 clerics, 4 or 5 wizards, 4 or 5 rogues/pallys/sks, that are 55+ then doing fear is probably not the best idea because you are asking for a lot of CR and unhappyness.<br>
<br>
The steps i posted dont always happen, but they sadly occur quite a bit.<br>
